# BMC Helix Innovation Studio — Requirement Gathering Questions

Use this guide to systematically gather requirements before building a **View Component** or **Java Service**. Start with Section 1 to determine the type, then proceed to the relevant section. Ask the questions conversationally — do not dump the entire list at once.

---

## Section 1: What Are You Building?

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 1.1 | What type of artifact do you want to build? | **View Component** (Angular UI in View Designer) · **Java Service** (Process Activity / REST API / Command) · **Both** (UI + backend service) |
| 1.2 | Give a one-sentence description of what it should do. | _e.g., "Display a Kanban board of ITSM tickets grouped by status"_ |
| 1.3 | What is the component/service name? (kebab-case) | _e.g., `ticket-kanban-board`, `incident-fetcher`_ |

---

## Section 2: View Component Questions

### 2A — Component Category & Layout

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 2A.1 | What category best describes your component? | **Data Table** (list of records) · **Create Form** (new record entry) · **Detail View** (view/edit single record) · **Kanban Board** (column-based layout) · **Dashboard / Chart** (data visualization) · **Interactive Utility** (calculator, converter, etc.) · **Display Only** (read-only info panel) · **Custom Widget** (other) |
| 2A.2 | Does the component need a title bar / header? | Yes / No |
| 2A.3 | Should users be able to hide/show the component conditionally? | Yes (standard props: hidden, CSS classes, device visibility) / No |
| 2A.4 | What View Designer group should it appear in? | _e.g., `Sample App`, `ITSM`, `Custom Components`_ |
| 2A.5 | What icon should represent it in the palette? | `table` · `edit` · `plus-circle` · `file-text` · `calculator` · `bar-chart` · `list` · `grid` · other |

### 2B — Data Source & Record Definition

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 2B.1 | Does the component interact with record data? | Yes / No (skip to 2C if No) |
| 2B.2 | Which record definition(s) does it use? | _e.g., `com.mycompany.sample-app:Contact Book`, `com.bmc.dsm.itsm-applications:ITSM Tickets CRD`_ |
| 2B.3 | Should the record definition be configurable via the Property Inspector, or hardcoded? | Configurable (text input in inspector) / Hardcoded |
| 2B.4 | What fields (by ID and name) should be displayed or used? | _e.g., `536870913=Name, 536870914=Phone, 536870915=Email`_ |
| 2B.5 | Does the component need standard system fields? (ID, Submitter, Create Date, Modified Date, Status, GUID) | Yes (include `1,2,3,5,6,7,8,16,379`) / Only specific ones / No |
| 2B.6 | Does the component call a **Java service** or **process** for its data (instead of direct REST)? | Yes (specify which) / No (direct DataPage API) |

### 2C — CRUD Operations

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 2C.1 | What operations does the component support? | **Read** (list/view) · **Create** (new records) · **Update** (edit existing) · **Delete** (remove records) · Multiple (specify) |
| 2C.2 | For **Create**: What fields should the form include? | _List field IDs, names, and types (text, number, date, dropdown, etc.)_ |
| 2C.3 | For **Create**: Which fields are required? | _List required field IDs_ |
| 2C.4 | For **Create**: Are there any validation rules? | _e.g., max length, regex pattern, numeric range_ |
| 2C.5 | For **Create**: Does the form need a reset/cancel button? | Yes / No |
| 2C.6 | For **Update**: Should editing be inline or in a separate form/modal? | Inline edit · Modal dialog · Separate detail view · Navigate to another view |
| 2C.7 | For **Delete**: Should there be a confirmation prompt? | Yes / No |
| 2C.8 | After a successful create/update/delete, what should happen? | Refresh the list · Show success message · Navigate somewhere · Emit event · Multiple |

### 2D — Filtering, Sorting & Pagination

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 2D.1 | Does the component need filtering? | Yes / No |
| 2D.2 | If yes, what fields should be filterable? | _e.g., Name (text search), Status (dropdown), Priority (dropdown)_ |
| 2D.3 | Should filters be shown/hidden via a toggle? | Yes (`showFilter` property in inspector) / Always visible / No filters |
| 2D.4 | Does the component need sorting? | Yes (specify sortable columns) / No |
| 2D.5 | Does the component need pagination? | Yes / No |
| 2D.6 | If yes, should page size be configurable? | Yes (inspector property) / Hardcoded (specify default) |
| 2D.7 | Default page size? | _e.g., 10, 25, 50, 100_ |

### 2E — Navigation & Drill-Down

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 2E.1 | Does the component need to navigate to a detail view? | Yes / No |
| 2E.2 | If yes, what is the target view/route? | _e.g., `#/com.mycompany.sample-app/preview/<view-name>?id=<recordId>`_ |
| 2E.3 | Does the component receive parameters from URL/query string? | Yes (specify param names) / No |
| 2E.4 | Should the component interact with other components on the same view? | Yes (via Set Property action, events) / No |

### 2F — Refresh & Auto-Update

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 2F.1 | Does the component need a manual refresh button? | Yes / No |
| 2F.2 | Does the component need auto-refresh on an interval? | Yes (configurable interval in inspector) / Yes (fixed interval) / No |
| 2F.3 | Default refresh interval (seconds)? | _e.g., 30, 60, 300_ |

### 2G — UI & Styling

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 2G.1 | Should the component use BMC UX Adapt components? | Yes (specify: adapt-table, adapt-charts, buttons, modals, tabs, alerts) / No (plain HTML/CSS) |
| 2G.2 | Does the component need loading indicators? | Yes (spinner, skeleton, progress bar) / No |
| 2G.3 | Does the component need empty state messaging? | Yes / No |
| 2G.4 | Does the component need error state display? | Yes (inline error banner) / No |
| 2G.5 | Does the component need status badges or color coding? | Yes (specify status-to-color mapping) / No |
| 2G.6 | Does the component need responsive/mobile support? | Yes / No |
| 2G.7 | Any specific branding/color requirements? | _Describe or reference_ |

### 2H — Property Inspector (Design-Time Configuration)

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 2H.1 | What properties should be configurable in the View Designer Property Inspector? | _List all configurable props with types_ |
| 2H.2 | For each property, what form control should be used? | `TextFormControlComponent` (text input) · `SwitchFormControlComponent` (toggle) · `NumberFormControlComponent` (number) · `SelectFormControlComponent` (dropdown) |
| 2H.3 | Should any properties support expression evaluation? | Yes (specify which — allows dynamic values from other components) / No |
| 2H.4 | Should the component expose a Set Property action? | Yes (specify settable properties) / No |
| 2H.5 | Should the component include standard props? (Hidden, CSS Classes, Device Visibility) | Yes / No |
| 2H.6 | What default values should properties have? | _e.g., title="My Component", pageSize="25", showFilter=true_ |

### 2I — Component API (Actions)

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 2I.1 | What API methods should the component expose to custom actions? | _e.g., `refresh()`, `reset()`, `getRecords()`, `createRecord()`_ |
| 2I.2 | Should the component emit events/notifications? | Yes (specify event names and payloads) / No |
| 2I.3 | Does the component need to call `notifyPropertyChanged` for expression bindings? | Yes (specify which properties) / No |

### 2J — Design-Time Preview

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 2J.1 | What should the component look like in the View Designer preview? | Realistic sample data · Simple placeholder text · Static mockup |
| 2J.2 | Should the design preview reflect inspector property changes in real-time? | Yes / No (static preview is fine) |

