## Section 3: Java Service Questions

### 3A — Service Type

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 3A.1 | What type of Java service are you building? | **Process Activity** (usable in BPMN processes and rules) · **REST API** (custom JAX-RS endpoint) · **Command** (fire-and-forget) · **DataPageQuery** (custom data source for views) |
| 3A.2 | Give a one-sentence description of what the service does. | _e.g., "Fetch incident details from HPD:Help Desk by incident ID"_ |
| 3A.3 | What is the service class name? (PascalCase) | _e.g., `IncidentFetcherProcessActivity`, `TicketListService`_ |
| 3A.4 | Should the service be registered as `Scope.PUBLIC`? | Yes (accessible from processes/rules) / No (internal only) |

### 3B — Inputs

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 3B.1 | What input parameters does the service accept? | _List each with: name, type (String, Integer, Long, Boolean), required/optional_ |
| 3B.2 | For each input, are there validation rules? | `@NotNull` · `@NotBlank` · Regex pattern · Min/Max value · Custom validation |
| 3B.3 | Do any inputs have default values? | _e.g., pageSize defaults to 10, startIndex defaults to 0_ |
| 3B.4 | Does the service accept a dynamic record definition name as input? | Yes (generic/reusable) / No (hardcoded record definition) |
| 3B.5 | Does the service accept a query expression for filtering? | Yes / No |

### 3C — Record/Data Operations

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 3C.1 | Does the service interact with record definitions? | Yes / No (skip to 3D if No) |
| 3C.2 | Which record definition(s) does it query? | _e.g., `HPD:Help Desk`, `com.mycompany.sample-app:Contact Book`, dynamic (from input)_ |
| 3C.3 | What operations does it perform? | **Query** (DataPage) · **Read** (single record by ID) · **Create** · **Update** · **Delete** · **Multi-step lookup** (chained queries) |
| 3C.4 | For **queries**: Which field IDs should be fetched? | _e.g., `1,7,8,379,536870913,536870914`_ |
| 3C.5 | For **queries**: Should the field list be configurable (input parameter) or hardcoded? | Configurable / Hardcoded |
| 3C.6 | For **queries**: Does it need pagination support (pageSize, startIndex)? | Yes / No |
| 3C.7 | For **multi-step lookups**: Describe the chain of queries. | _e.g., "Step 1: Fetch incident, get ServiceCI_ReconID. Step 2: Query AST:Attributes with that ID, get impact"_ |
| 3C.8 | Does the service need to create or update records? | Yes (specify which fields to set) / No |

### 3D — Output / Response

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 3D.1 | What should the service return? | **Simple value** (String, number) · **Response DTO** (structured object) · **Markdown table** (for display in processes) · **JSON payload** |
| 3D.2 | If a Response DTO, what fields should it contain? | _List each with: name, type, description_ |
| 3D.3 | Should the response always include `success` (boolean) and `errorMessage` (String)? | Yes (recommended) / No |
| 3D.4 | For table output: What columns should the markdown table include? | _List column headers and corresponding field IDs_ |
| 3D.5 | Does the service return a count of records? | Yes (`recordCount` field) / No |

### 3E — Error Handling

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 3E.1 | How should errors be handled? | Return error in response DTO (set `success=false`, `errorMessage`) · Throw exception · Log and return empty result |
| 3E.2 | Should specific error scenarios be handled differently? | _e.g., "Record not found: return empty with specific message", "Permission denied: specific error code"_ |
| 3E.3 | What logging level should be used? | Debug (inputs/internals) · Info (success/counts) · Warn (edge cases) · Error (exceptions) |

### 3F — External Integrations

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 3F.1 | Does the service call any external APIs (non-BMC)? | Yes (specify URL, auth method, payload) / No |
| 3F.2 | Does the service call other BMC Helix services or processes? | Yes (specify which) / No |
| 3F.3 | Does the service need HTTP client capabilities? | Yes (REST calls to external systems) / No (RecordService only) |

### 3G — Process Definition

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 3G.1 | Does this service need a Process Definition (`.def` file) to be callable from views/rules? | Yes / No (REST API doesn't need one) |
| 3G.2 | If yes, what should the process name be? | _e.g., `com.mycompany.sample-app:fetchIncident`_ |
| 3G.3 | Should the process have the same input/output parameters as the Java service? | Yes (mirror all params) / Subset (specify which) |

### 3H — Performance & Limits

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 3H.1 | What is the expected data volume? | Small (< 100 records) · Medium (100–10,000) · Large (> 10,000) |
| 3H.2 | Should there be a maximum page size or result limit? | Yes (specify max) / No |
| 3H.3 | Is the operation expected to be long-running? | Yes (consider async) / No (synchronous is fine) |

---

## Section 4: Both (View Component + Java Service)

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 4.1 | Does the view component call the Java service directly via REST, or through a Process? | Direct REST call · Via Process (process definition needed) · Via DataPage API |
| 4.2 | How does data flow between them? | Component > REST call > Java service > Response DTO > Component renders |
| 4.3 | Should the Java service be reusable by other components/processes? | Yes (generic inputs, `Scope.PUBLIC`) / No (tightly coupled to this component) |
| 4.4 | Are there shared data structures (field IDs, constants) between frontend and backend? | Yes (document them) / No |

---

## Section 5: Deployment & Testing

| # | Question | Options / Examples |
|---|----------|--------------------|
| 5.1 | Target environment? | Docker dev container · Remote BMC Helix server · Both |
| 5.2 | Do you need the dev server for live reload during development? | Yes (`nx serve shell`) / No (build and deploy each time) |
| 5.3 | Are there existing components/services to use as reference? | Yes (specify which) / No |
| 5.4 | Priority: speed of delivery or code quality/completeness? | Speed (MVP first) · Quality (full error handling, tests, polish) · Balanced |

